item.title: I dont get it
item.dc:creator: @I_Br3ndan_I I Br3ndan I
item.description:
@I_Br3ndan_I wrote:

1st of all. Once you’ve checked all the No-IP domain(s) in the No-IP DUC, go into you’re source file, be it Testscape, Pimpscape whatever. Double-click runserver.bat and you’re server should be running fine.

To ‘update’, once you’ve changed something make sure you compile. If you have any errors in a particular file, say client.java, you can’t ‘update’ anything unless you’ve fixed those.

Tell me if you don’t understand.
